        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 9:42PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 941 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Southern Pines, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Cary, Sanford, Southern Pines, Raeford, Pittsboro,
Lillington, Carthage, Fort Bragg, and Garner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
